author: Suhas Nayse
title: Rahul Club shock Rabbani in NDFA Elite Division League Football
text:
NAGPUR: An early goal helped Rahul Club surprise formidable Rabbani Club in the Meghe NDFA Elite Division Football League match at the Police Line Takli ground here on Wednesday.
Mohd Shafeeque slammed a brilliant goal in the eighth minute which turned out to be a match-winning effort. The Kamptee powerhouse tried desperately to restore parity but all their moves bore no fruits.
In the Super Division League, Nagpur Blues hammered Anjuman Sporting Club 7-1. Amol Roy struck a brace, while Kundal Sharma, Mujahid, Karan Kanojia, Pratik Chimankar and Robert chipped in with a goal apiece to enable Blues register a thumping victory. Abhijeet Kshirsagar scored a consolation goal for Anjuman.
Nagpur City 'A' crushed Central Railway Institute 5-0, courtesy a brace by Sumeet Gawande.
RESULTS
Elite Division: Rahul SS 1 (Mohd Shafeeque 8th min) bt Rabbani Club 0.
Super Division: Nagpur Blues 7 (Kundal Sharma 21st min, Amol Roy 23rd min, 75th min, Mujahid 41st min, Karan Kanojia 51st min, Pratik Chimankar 60th min, Robert 84th min) bt Anjuman SC 1 (Abhijeet Kshirsagar 64th min).
Senior Division: Nagpur City 'A' 5 (Rahul Saini 11th min, Sumeet Gawande 14th min, 23rd min, Sameer Sheikh 20th min, Mohd Mujahid 85th min) bt CR Institute 0.
On Thursday
Elite Division: Young Iqbal vs DSA C Rly at Police Line Takli ground (3 pm).
Senior Division: Nagpur Star vs Shakti Sporting at Police Line Takli ground (1.30 pm).
